@startuml ClaudeCodeEgressTopology
!includeurl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/proveo-ca/identity/refs/heads/main/proveo.iuml
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam linetype ortho

left to right direction

title Claude Code Egress Topology — Go-Inspector Firewall + Credential Broker

actor "Human" as Human
actor "Claude Code" as Claude

package "Mode: open" as OpenMode {
  component "claudecode\n--dangerously-skip-permissions" as OpenClaude <<container>>
  component "default bridge\ndirect internet" as OpenBridge <<network>>
}

package "Mode: proxy" as ProxyMode {
  component "claudecode\ninternal only" as ProxyClaude <<container>>
  component "squid:3128\nHTTP(S) enforcement" as ProxySquid <<container>>
  component "egress network" as ProxyEgress <<network>>
}

package "Mode: firewall" as FirewallMode {
  component "claudecode\ninternal only" as FirewallClaude <<container>>
  component "agent-inspect-net\ninternal" as AgentInspectNet <<network>>
  component "proveo-egress:8888\nGo MITM: record + broker\n(mitmproxy = legacy fallback)" as Mitm <<container>>
  component "broker secret env-file\n0600, outside agent mounts" as CredFile <<storage>>
  component "inspect-enforce-net\ninternal" as InspectEnforceNet <<network>>
  component "squid:3128\nupstream policy proxy" as Squid <<container>>
  component "egress-net\ninternet capable" as EgressNet <<network>>
  component "ollama:11434\nlocal model (optional)" as Ollama <<container>>
}

package "Observability" as Observability {
  component "mitmproxy flows\nNDJSON (decrypted)" as MitmFlows <<storage>>
  component "Squid access.log\nallow / deny" as SquidLogs <<storage>>
  component "Egress guard reject.log\nraw protocol bypass attempts" as GuardLogs <<storage>>
  component "Vite + Node dashboard\nnormalized event timeline" as Dashboard <<app>>
  component "post-run report\ntop 5 allowed / top 5 denied" as Report <<storage>>
}

package "Internet" as Internet {
  component "LLM providers\nAnthropic, etc." as Providers <<external>>
  component "Docs / search / package metadata\nany HTTP(S) read target" as ReadWeb <<external>>
  component "Blocked writes / uploads / pushes" as BlockedWrites <<external>>
  component "Blocked non-web protocols\nFTP, SSH, DB, mail, raw TCP/UDP" as BlockedProtocols <<external>>
}

Claude --> OpenClaude : open mode
OpenClaude --> OpenBridge : unrestricted egress
OpenBridge --> Internet : direct

Claude --> ProxyClaude : proxy mode
ProxyClaude --> ProxySquid : HTTP_PROXY / HTTPS_PROXY
ProxySquid --> ProxyEgress
ProxyEgress --> Providers : allowed exceptions
ProxyEgress --> ReadWeb : allowed HTTP(S) reads
ProxySquid -[#red]-> BlockedWrites : deny where observable

Claude --> FirewallClaude : firewall mode
FirewallClaude ..> Ollama : NO_PROXY direct (local model, no egress)
FirewallClaude --> AgentInspectNet : HTTP_PROXY / HTTPS_PROXY + trusts mitm CA
AgentInspectNet --> Mitm : first hop decrypts HTTP(S)
CredFile ..> Mitm : real provider secret (sidecar only)
Mitm --> MitmFlows : record / export NDJSON (no query string)
Mitm -[#005F7F,bold]-> Providers : inject real credential (pinned host only)
Mitm -[#6E1100,bold]-> BlockedWrites : strip credential headers (all other hosts)
Mitm --> InspectEnforceNet : upstream proxy only
InspectEnforceNet --> Squid : enforce policy
Squid --> SquidLogs : allow / deny log
Squid --> EgressNet : only real internet egress
EgressNet --> Providers : allowed exceptions
EgressNet --> ReadWeb : allowed HTTP(S) reads
Squid -[#red]-> BlockedWrites : deny where observable
FirewallClaude -[#red]-> GuardLogs : direct non-web bypass attempts
GuardLogs -[#red]-> BlockedProtocols : deny + log

MitmFlows --> Dashboard
SquidLogs --> Dashboard
GuardLogs --> Dashboard
SquidLogs ..> Report : summarized on container exit
Human --> Dashboard : inspect agent egress timeline
Human ..> Report : top allowed / denied egress

note right of Mitm
""proveo-egress"" (Go, martian) is the first-hop
inspector. HTTPS interception is on: it decrypts
and records each request (method / path / host,
**no query string**) as NDJSON. The agent trusts
its generated CA via standard CA env vars, so all
its TLS terminates here; it uses Squid as upstream
proxy and has no direct internet egress. Runs as
the invoking host uid, not root.
**Credential broker** (firewall only):
the real provider secret lives ONLY in this
sidecar (0600 env-file, outside agent mounts). It
**injects** the auth header on the pinned-provider
host and **strips** credential headers everywhere
else, so a key the agent read from a mounted
""\.env"" is useless for exfiltration.
(""PROVEO_EGRESS_INSPECTOR=mitmproxy"" selects the
legacy Python sidecar, without the broker.)
end note

note right of Squid
Squid is the enforcement proxy:
- allow HTTP :80
- allow HTTPS CONNECT :443
- allow GET/HEAD/OPTIONS by default
- allow provider API exceptions
- deny reserved/private/bogon destinations
  with FireHOL-informed built-in defaults
- optionally include generated FireHOL
  blocklist-ipsets such as firehol_level1
- deny FTP, SSH, DB, mail, Redis,
  Docker daemon, and raw TCP/UDP by topology
Squid sees only CONNECT host:port for HTTPS;
mitmproxy provides the decrypted method/path view.
end note

note bottom of FirewallMode
Docker network invariant:
claudecode only reaches mitmproxy.
mitmproxy only reaches Squid.
Only Squid has internet-capable egress.
Proxy env vars are not the boundary;
network attachment is the boundary.
end note

note bottom of Observability
Dashboard normalizes mitmproxy flow exports,
Squid access logs, and guard reject logs into
one human-readable timeline of allowed,
blocked, and bypass-attempted egress.
When the agent container exits, the lifecycle
also writes a ""report.txt""/""report.json"" with the
top 5 allowed external operations and top 5 denied,
summarized from the Squid access log.
end note

note bottom of Ollama
Optional ""--local-model"" (e.g. gemma4): an Ollama
sidecar on the agent network serving the host's
already-pulled models, read-only and offline.
Reached directly via ""NO_PROXY"", so its traffic
never touches mitmproxy or Squid — the local model
works while all internet egress stays policed.
end note

note right of Providers
**Provider egress allowlist** (proxy + firewall).
Auto-detected from the present API key: inference
WRITES (POST/...) are pinned to the chosen provider
endpoint only; web READS (docs/search/scraping)
stay open; writes to any other host are denied.
Endpoint map: Bedrock/Azure/Vertex (tight regex),
Together/Fireworks/GMI/OpenRouter, and native
Anthropic/OpenAI/xAI/Perplexity/Google/Groq/Mistral/Cohere.
""update-provider-allow.sh"" reconciles the map vs LiteLLM.
end note

note bottom of Internet
Two egress-layer purposes:
1. No irreversible action without HITL — only the
   provider may receive writes; pushes/publishes/writes
   elsewhere are denied and logged.
2. No leaks to providers — inference is pinned to the
   chosen endpoint, so data can't be POSTed to an
   arbitrary host. Reads stay open so agents can research.
end note

@enduml
